<br>
This is a technique that has been successful in the past (for example, one of these markets predicted the day that Saddam would fall before the war, and they have had similar successes in less intense fields like sports and show business). DARPA is trying to investigate possible intelligence tools more efficient than paying bajillions of dollars for a spy agency that can't even catch terrorists who live in the house of one of their informants for a few months, they consider this a promising lead, and I think it's good that they're looking into it. <br>
The reasons people have proposed against it are generally pretty silly - we may have some pretty stupid people, but I don't think anyone's going to think &quot;Hey! I can make five dollars fifty cents if Arafat dies! Lemme buy a gun and take the next plane to Ramallah!&quot; I think the only real argument against it is that it seems sort of sick in an intangible sort of way - but if it could save lives, who cares? As [let's play the identify the quote game here!] said, &quot;He who denies himself a useful tool because it reminds him of his own mortality has needlessly and pointlessly crippled himself&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E4705><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmenelmacar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevonandarosel>Trevon Andarosel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://elektron.its.tudelft.nl/~maernst/umb_icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Something with Umbagollah<br> Istvanistani Chaocrat<br>
Trusted Friend</span><br> <font color=#FF9300>(7/30/03 3:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://elektron.its.tudelft.nl/~maernst/pergament3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is Sick...</span><hr size=1> I think this stock-market can be very accurate because it will work as a self-fullfilling prophecy. Not because someone just decides from one day to the next &quot;hey, let's kill the president&quot;, but it may work as extra incentive for people who do plan certain actions to increase their efforts to do it on a certain day. <br>
<br>
Trevon. <p>The storyteller of Ex, <A href="http://www.umbagollah.com">Umbagollah</a><BR>
