<br>
Now DARPA is a very powerful agency, brilliant, controlling, with many intelligent individuals.  All my respect for good shadow government skills goes to DARPA.<br>
<br>
The reason I view it as sick is you are betting on human life.  It reminds me more of cock fighting then it does the stock market from what I've read.<br>
<br>
Basically investors make bets on dates/deeds and if they come true they get money.  I'm all for legalizing gambling and I see nothing illegal about this.  On a morale level I do not appreciate betting on human life to make money. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E4705><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmenelmacar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solarwinds23>SolarWinds23</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MAA S1 Champion<br>
Enlightened One</span><br> <font color=#FF9300>(7/30/03 1:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Darpa</span><hr size=1> I'm with Archetype on this one, and not just for moral reasons.  (Although the thought of saying &quot;Yeah, my financial future is heavily reliant on [insert world leader] being assassinated within the next year&quot; does make me a bit sick.)<br>
<br>
I wouldn't worry about some hick with a sawed off shotgun and $5.50 on Arafat for the 15th jumping a plane to the Middle East, but I do think it would give terrorist organizations and large crime syndicates incentive.  Instead of spending a lot of money to carry out a plot, they could be making money.  <br>
<br>
They'd simply place their &quot;bets&quot; at the last possible moment, depriving the authorities of enough time to respond and prevent the attack/assassination, etc.  So yeah, they might get a few days warning-- depending on whether they require you to get in the market a certain amount of time before the day you suspect the act-- but probably not enough time to properly respond.  Also, to make the market sensitive enough to be practical, they wouldn't want to put a long wait period on bets as that would eliminate last-minute tips that could be vital. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E4705><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmenelmacar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scottsiskind>Scott Siskind</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://squid314.homestead.com/files/littleicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Friend</span><br> <font color=#FF9300>(7/30/03 9:10 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://squid314.homestead.com/files/littlescott.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Darpa</span><hr size=1> Well, personally I can't find an action morally wrong if it doesn't actually hurt anyone, and I can stomach a loss of principle if it might save people's lives.<br>
